UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Byron Owen SEWELL by His Guardian, Farmers’ & Merchants’ National Bank of Los Angeles, Appellee. No. 7393. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Feb. 7, 1934. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and M. G. Gallaher, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los Angeles, Cal. Chenoweth & Whitehead, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and GARRECHT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

TT ,4. Upon stipulation of counsel for respee-tive parties, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
